Program: Omnibus
Title: First Tourists in the Alps
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376lr0
Last Broadcast Date: 25 August 1998
Recreating William Windham's journey up the Mer de Glace near Chamonix in the Alps. His walk was made at a time when locals never went up the glacier, believeing it to be populated by monsters. The expedition led to the development of mountain hiking and skiing tourism .